santa barbara energy summit 2010 precourt energy efficiency center peec stanford university peec logo mission contact us stanford university home buildings transportation systems behavior modeling policy people at peec peec's mission research at peec events news library affiliate program directions and parking santa barbara summit on energy efficiency may 12 13 2010 santa barbara ca http iee ucsb edu sbsee2010 sponsored by the institute for energy efficiency iee at the university of california santa barbara contact whitney wegener 805 893 5496 the santa barbara summit on energy efficiency will bring together global leaders and stakeholders in energy efficiency technology implementation business and policy for two days of in depth discussions and industry updates in this fast moving sector the summit agenda will focus on the most promising energy efficiency technology developments and their implementation along with the role of government in fostering innovation and commercialization providing an opportunity to learn about the latest technology and policy developments in energy production and storage lighting buildings computing and electronics keynote speakers include dan reicher director of climate change and energy initiatives at google richard newell administrator of the us energy information administration and michael peevey president of the california public utilities commission more information related links upcoming events past events precourt energy efficiency center copyright 2011 stanford university
